–block


Dr. Pierre Menard (the head of the Pataphysics Department, and the author of all the footnotes) is, in actuality, Don Quixote  Don Quixote's long-suffering squire (now a valiant knight himself). The article is effectively a protracted rescue mission carried out by Sancho to re-ignite the sense of adventure of his old master, who has given up his dreams and become a depressing, cynical busy-body who works for the Foundation's Pataphysics Department.

In the first iteration, Alonso (again, this is Sancho, remember) infects fiction after he discovers the Foundation from Fred (and realizes that clearly, his old Master has been 'kidnapped' by them). He's basically accelerating through fiction, trying to reach the Foundation.

In the second iteration, he's managed to do it  is responsible for editing and writing). Bloodied and nearly dead, he offers his sword to his old Master, who embraces his near-dead squire.

The final iteration is meant to imply that Pierre has returned to his old ways, alongside his squire  now as windmill keepers, where they regularly attack the windmills (on account of suspecting they might be giants).










